           <div type="translation" source="bib:Chhom2011_01"><!-- kuch: The term 'slave' should be understood as 'servant'. -->
 	<p n="1-17">Village of <gap reason="lost"/>: Si Kaṁpat, Si Kañcū, Gho Kanras, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Krau, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Aṁvil, Gvāl Chpoṅ, Gvāl Pan-u, Gvāl <gap reason="lost"/> Vraḥ Prasāda, Tai Kanteṅ, Tai Kaṁpit <gap reason="lost"/> R̥ddhi, Tai A Kapa<gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Dharmma, Tai <gap reason="lost"/> accompanied by daughter(s) <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai pau</foreign></supplied> <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Sraṅe, Tai Panlas, Tai Kaṁpit, <gap reason="lost"/> accompanied by a daughter <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai rat</foreign></supplied> called <gap reason="lost"/> Kanso, <gap reason="lost"/>, 5 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, 4 animal keepers <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gvāl</foreign></supplied>, 10 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied> <gap reason="lost"/>, a baby girl, <gap reason="lost"/>; grand total <gap reason="lost"/> Vandha, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Hari, <gap reason="lost"/> accompanied by a child <supplied reason="explanation">or children</supplied>, <gap reason="lost"/> Cancān, <gap reason="lost"/> Tai Saṁ-ap, Tai Laṅgāy, <gap reason="lost"/> accompanied by a son <supplied reason="explanation">or sons</supplied> <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied> <gap reason="lost"/> accompanied by a daughter <supplied reason="explanation">or dallghters</supplied> <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai pau</foreign></supplied> <gap reason="lost"/>. Total: 4 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, 4 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>, 2 boys <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied>, a baby girl <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai pau</foreign></supplied>; grand total <gap reason="lost"/>.</p>
              <p n="17-20"><gap reason="lost"/>, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Si <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>.</p>
              <p n="20-25">Village of <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gvāl Krau, Gvāl <gap reason="lost"/> Kaṁvrau, Si <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Thleṁ, Tai <gap reason="lost"/></p>
